  "chapter": {
    "bookTitle": "James",
    "delineation": "Chapter",
    "number": 2,
    "summary": "God has chosen the poor of this world who are rich in faith—Salvation is gained by keeping the whole law—Faith without works is dead.",
    "chapterAugmentations": [],
    "verses": [
      {
        "text": "My brethren, have not the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with respect of persons.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "GR not with partiality, have the faith of our Lord. JST James 2:1 … ye cannot have the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, and yet have respect to persons.",
            "start": 13,
            "end": 17
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Jesus Christ, Lord.",
            "start": 39,
            "end": 56
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 58,
            "end": 66
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For if there come unto your assembly a man with a gold ring, in goodly apparel, and there come in also a poor man in vile raiment;",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Poor.",
            "start": 105,
            "end": 109
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR dirty.",
            "start": 117,
            "end": 121
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And ye have respect to him that weareth the gay clothing, and say unto him, Sit thou here in a good place; and say to the poor, Stand thou there, or sit here under my footstool:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "GR splendid.",
            "start": 44,
            "end": 47
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Are ye not then partial in yourselves, and are become judges of evil thoughts?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 2:4 Are ye not then in yourselves partial judges, and become evil in your thoughts?",
            "start": 0,
            "end": 3
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Hearken, my beloved brethren, Hath not God chosen the poor of this world rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom which he hath promised to them that love him?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Prov. 15:16; Matt. 5:3; Luke 6:20; 1 Cor. 1:27 (27–28). TG Poor.",
            "start": 54,
            "end": 58
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But ye have despised the poor. Do not rich men oppress you, and draw you before the judgment seats?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Oppression.",
            "start": 47,
            "end": 54
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Do not they blaspheme that worthy name by the which ye are called?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Name.",
            "start": 34,
            "end": 38
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "If ye fulfil the royal law according to the scripture, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself, ye do well:",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Love.",
            "start": 66,
            "end": 70
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Neighbor.",
            "start": 75,
            "end": 84
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But if ye have respect to persons, ye commit sin, and are convinced of the law as transgressors.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Deut. 1:17; Prov. 28:21.",
            "start": 15,
            "end": 22
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For whosoever shall keep the whole law, and yet offend in one point, he is guilty of all.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 50:28 (28–29).",
            "start": 29,
            "end": 34
          },
          {
            "footnote": "GR stumble, err. TG Offense; Sin.",
            "start": 48,
            "end": 54
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Guilt.",
            "start": 75,
            "end": 81
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 62,
            "end": 68
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For he that said, Do not commit adultery, said also, Do not kill. Now if thou commit no adultery, yet if thou kill, thou art become a transgressor of the law.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Adulterer.",
            "start": 32,
            "end": 40
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "So speak ye, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Liberty.",
            "start": 67,
            "end": 74
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "For he shall have judgment without mercy, that hath shewed no mercy; and mercy rejoiceth against judgment.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Ps. 109:7.",
            "start": 18,
            "end": 26
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Mercy.",
            "start": 35,
            "end": 40
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "What doth it profit, my brethren, though a man say he hath faith, and have not works? can faith save him?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 2:14–21 (Appendix).",
            "start": 0,
            "end": 4
          },
          {
            "footnote": "D&C 20:69.",
            "start": 59,
            "end": 64
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 5,
            "end": 12
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "If a brother or sister be naked, and destitute of daily food,",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Brotherhood and Sisterhood.",
            "start": 5,
            "end": 12
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Food.",
            "start": 56,
            "end": 60
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And one of you say unto them, Depart in peace, be ye warmed and filled; notwithstanding ye give them not those things which are needful to the body; what doth it profit?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Luke 3:11 (8–14); D&C 104:18.",
            "start": 91,
            "end": 95
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 50,
            "end": 52
          },
          {
            "start": 154,
            "end": 161
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Even so faith, if it hath not works, is dead, being alone.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "1 Thes. 1:3.",
            "start": 8,
            "end": 13
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Obedience.",
            "start": 30,
            "end": 35
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Yea, a man may say, Thou hast faith, and I have works: shew me thy faith without thy works, and I will shew thee my faith by my works.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Faith.",
            "start": 116,
            "end": 121
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Matt. 7:20 (15–20); D&C 20:37.",
            "start": 128,
            "end": 133
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Thou believest that there is one God; thou doest well: the devils also believe, and tremble.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "JST James 2:19 … devils also believe, and tremble; thou hast made thyself like unto them, not being justified. Acts 16:17.",
            "start": 59,
            "end": 65
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Luke 8:28 (27–28).",
            "start": 71,
            "end": 78
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "But wilt thou know, O vain man, that faith without works is dead?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Faith.",
            "start": 37,
            "end": 42
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Prov. 24:12.",
            "start": 51,
            "end": 56
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Was not Abraham our father justified by works, when he had offered Isaac his son upon the altar?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Heb. 11:17.",
            "start": 27,
            "end": 36
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Gen. 22:9 (9–12).",
            "start": 59,
            "end": 66
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Seest thou how faith wrought with his works, and by works was faith made perfect?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Good Works.",
            "start": 52,
            "end": 57
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Perfection.",
            "start": 73,
            "end": 80
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "And the scripture was fulfilled which saith, Abraham believed God, and it was imputed unto him for righteousness: and he was called the Friend of God.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Gen. 22:12. TG Faith.",
            "start": 53,
            "end": 61
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Righteousness.",
            "start": 99,
            "end": 112
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Isa. 41:8. TG Friendship.",
            "start": 136,
            "end": 142
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Ye see then how that by works a man is justified, and not by faith only.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "2 Ne. 25:23. TG Commitment.",
            "start": 24,
            "end": 29
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Justification.",
            "start": 39,
            "end": 48
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      },
      {
        "text": "Likewise also was not Rahab the harlot justified by works, when she had received the messengers, and had sent them out another way?",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "Josh. 2:1.",
            "start": 22,
            "end": 27
          },
          {
            "footnote": "Heb. 11:31.",
            "start": 39,
            "end": 48
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": [
          {
            "start": 110,
            "end": 114
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead also.",
        "footnotes": [
          {
            "footnote": "TG Spirit Body; Spirits, Disembodied.",
            "start": 28,
            "end": 34
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Death.",
            "start": 38,
            "end": 42
          },
          {
            "footnote": "TG Good Works.",
            "start": 61,
            "end": 66
          }
        ],
        "associatedContents": [],
        "italics": []
      }
    ]
  }
}